pull.title: Upgrade mac_alias to 2.0.7
pull.body:
The patch Bitcoin Core has been maintaining for mac_alias was pulled by the mac_alias maintainer in commit 4f31cb084c1c6a8626128b0b00842020b6db9037. Delete the patch and remove the patch from the depends system.

Note that this PR won't be complete until a new version of mac_alias containing the patch has been released, and the depends system is updated to reflect the new version.

events.body: Just for reference, [here's the original PR for the mac_alias patch](https://github.com/al45tair/mac_alias/pull/3).

events.body: Added a commit upgrading mac_alias to 2.0.7 and did `make deploy` on my Macbook Pro. The resultant DMG file allowed me to place Core in /Applications. Core runs fine. Background image of the DMG looks fine. A couple of the icons are in weird spots but this is apparently normal. Besides, as mentioned, the core functionality is present.
Looks good to me, @theuni might want to sign off on this because it's a depends change.

utACK https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/12417/commits/fc1bfcf9fd2c24846a9f9caa42f5370f192c3d40

@droark Could you post a screenshot of the out of place icons for reference?
@droark You just have hidden files showing. That's normal.

@theuni - Oh no, I understand the hidden folders. :) I just seemed to recall some issue/PR from awhile back where something similar was discussed, and how the macOS builds put the icons in odd places. I thought it had been resolved? I can't remember where I saw all this, though, and I could be wrong. Better safe than sorry!

**EDIT**: Again, just to be clear, I was able to install the build without any problems, and I ran it for awhile on my Mac. This is purely a cosmetic issue, AFAIK. I wouldn't have even brought it up were it not for this being a depends upgrade.
@droark what version of macOS are you using?

issue.title: Remove Python2 support
issue.body:
Following discussion here: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/11843#issuecomment-351033742

It's easier for maintainers if all python tools/scripts support only a single version of Python. There are only a few scripts that aren't explicitly python3 at this point, so this PR changes those remaining scripts to explicitly require python3.

issue.title: Native ds_store python package is not python3 compatible
issue.body:
This tools is required to build a OSX disk image (`make deploy`).
https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/a6a860796a44a2805a58391a009ba22752f64e32/depends/packages/native_ds_store.mk

The tool is currently not python3 compatible (uses `basestring`).

Upstream:
https://bitbucket.org/al45tair/ds_store/
